## Content
````
The file `samples\getting_started\agents\openai\openai_chat_client_with_local_mcp.py` is designed to demonstrate the integration of the OpenAI Chat Client with Model Context Protocol (MCP) tools using a framework provided by Microsoft's agent framework library. It highlights the extended functionality and service access offered by combining these two technologies. Specifically, this script utilizes the enhanced metadata capabilities of MCP tools such as error states, token usage, and costs, extracted through the `_meta` field of `CallToolResult` objects.

The file contains two main asynchronous functions: `mcp_tools_on_run_level` and `mcp_tools_on_agent_level`. The function `samples.getting_started.agents.openai.openai_chat_client_with_local_mcp.mcp_tools_on_run_level` sets up MCP tools at the run level, requiring the tools to be connected to an MCP server before initiating the agent with these tools. The second function, `samples.getting_started.agents.openai.openai_chat_client_with_local_mcp.mcp_tools_on_agent_level`, configures the tools when creating the agent, enabling continuous access to tools during the agent's lifetime. Both functions utilize `MCPStreamableHTTPTool` and `ChatAgent`, or `OpenAIChatClient.create_agent`, to integrate MCP tools and create a helpful assistant capable of handling Microsoft's documentation questions. 

The script is executed sequentially with `samples.getting_started.agents.openai.openai_chat_client_with_local_mcp.main`, which first runs `mcp_tools_on_agent_level`, followed by `mcp_tools_on_run_level`. The implementation is initiated by `if __name__ == "__main__": asyncio.run(main())`, utilizing Python's `asyncio` for asynchronous execution.

Dependencies include the `agent_framework` library, specifically bringing in `ChatAgent` and `MCPStreamableHTTPTool`, and `OpenAIChatClient` from `agent_framework.openai`. The file is structured to illustrate the different stages at which MCP tools can be integrated and executed with the OpenAI Chat Client, focusing on demonstrating real-world usage for engineers needing to extend OpenAI capabilities with MCP enhancements.
````
